  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-2 mb-8">
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2">How long does a technical SEO audit take for a Swansea business?</summary>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-2">A full technical SEO audit typically takes 5 to 10 working days depending on the size and complexity of your website. Small brochure sites with under 50 pages are usually completed within a week, while larger e-commerce sites or platforms with thousands of URLs may take up to two weeks for a thorough crawl, analysis, and prioritised report.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2">What Core Web Vitals scores should my Swansea website aim for?</summary>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-2">Google recommends a Largest Contentful Paint under 2.5 seconds, a Cumulative Layout Shift below 0.1, and an Interaction to Next Paint under 200 milliseconds. These thresholds apply equally whether your customers are browsing from Mumbles on mobile data or from an office at SA1 Waterfront on fibre broadband.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-900 py-2">Does technical SEO affect local search rankings in Swansea?</summary>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-2">Yes. Google uses page speed, mobile usability, HTTPS status, and structured data as ranking signals for local results. A Swansea business with a fast, mobile-friendly, properly indexed site will consistently outrank a competitor with the same content but poor technical foundations in the Swansea local pack and map results.</p>
    </details>

